Tried the food when they were still new, not bad.  Tried it recently since minor renovations, enabling more counter space.  Mediocre tasting at best, prices a little steep.  The curry goat could be better flavored and for the price, too light on the meat and heavy on the Rice.  (It's Curry GOAT not curry Rice)  3-4-21 Update So I happened to give this another go I ordered the same thing I did when I did the first review.  The darker complexion lady who brings items from the kitchen is obnoxious.  She gave me another round of more rice and less meat, asked for plantain and she insisted it's not included.  (one piece was put in) and then says $10 for the whole order.  DON'T GET ROBBED go to Peppa's or Silver's Crust.  I will not return there with my last $5 bill.

Very old school spot. Grew up here and the food has been stellar. It's been under three managers and has been dishing out great food. There was a violation a long time ago but since then it's been really clean. The new food they serve such as veggie chunks , patties and BBQ chicken gourmet is really a welcomed change. There is also new salad options! Most Jamaican restaurants only serve steam cabbage and or the cheap tomato and cucumber carrot combo. Really proud of the place being around so long.  P.S. ask for mum's she's really great and serves lots of food.
